{"parents": [{"link": "../../documentation/", "title": "Documentation"}, {"link": "../", "title": "Command Line Utilities Reference"}], "prev": {"link": "../CombinedWorkflow/", "title": "CombinedWorkflow"}, "next": {"link": "../MaskFlow/", "title": "MaskFlow"}, "title": "MedianOtsuFlow", "meta": {}, "body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"medianotsuflow\">\n<h1>MedianOtsuFlow<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#medianotsuflow\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<div class=\"highlight-default\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span>Workflow wrapping the median_otsu segmentation method.\n\nApplies median_otsu segmentation on each file found by &#39;globing&#39;\n``input_files`` and saves the results in a directory specified by\n``out_dir``.\n\nParameters\n----------\ninput_files : string\n    Path to the input volumes. This path may contain wildcards to\n    process multiple inputs at once.\nsave_masked : bool\n    Save mask\nmedian_radius : int, optional\n    Radius (in voxels) of the applied median filter (default 2)\nnumpass : int, optional\n    Number of pass of the median filter (default 5)\nautocrop : bool, optional\n    If True, the masked input_volumes will also be cropped using the\n    bounding box defined by the masked data. For example, if diffusion\n    images are of 1x1x1 (mm^3) or higher resolution auto-cropping could\n    reduce their size in memory and speed up some of the analysis.\n    (default False)\nvol_idx : string, optional\n    1D array representing indices of ``axis=3`` of a 4D `input_volume`\n    &#39;None&#39; (the default) corresponds to ``(0,)`` (assumes first volume\n    in 4D array)\ndilate : string, optional\n    number of iterations for binary dilation (default &#39;None&#39;)\nout_dir : string, optional\n    Output directory (default input file directory)\nout_mask : string, optional\n    Name of the mask volume to be saved (default &#39;brain_mask.nii.gz&#39;)\nout_masked : string, optional\n    Name of the masked volume to be saved (default &#39;dwi_masked.nii.gz&#39;)\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "metatags": "", "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["reference_cmd/MaskFlow", "MaskFlow", "N", "next"], ["reference_cmd/CombinedWorkflow", "CombinedWorkflow", "P", "previous"]], "sourcename": "reference_cmd/MedianOtsuFlow.rst.txt", "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#\">MedianOtsuFlow</a></li>\n</ul>\n", "display_toc": false, "page_source_suffix": ".rst", "current_page_name": "reference_cmd/MedianOtsuFlow", "sidebars": null, "customsidebar": null, "alabaster_version": "0.7.10"}